Diego's game was simple: a roguelike dungeon crawler where weapons were Base NFTs. Die, and your sword goes to whoever killed you — on-chain, no tricks. Players hated losing gear. They also couldn't stop playing. His Discord went from 12 friends to 4,000 strangers in two months. A VC messaged him about a term sheet. He read it twice, then opened his game and played for an hour first. He wanted to remember why he built it.

